#!/bin/sh
# postinstall — write the setup checklist into the installed bundle.
# Runs as the installing user (per-user domain install).
set -euo pipefail

BUNDLE="$HOME/Applications/Boss.app"
RESOURCES="$BUNDLE/Contents/Resources"

cat > "$RESOURCES/SETUP.txt" << 'EOF'
Boss Setup Checklist
====================

Required tools (Boss will not start without these):

  cube   workspace management (https://github.com/spinyfin/cube)
         Install: cargo install cube  OR  pre-built binary from releases

  jj     Jujutsu VCS — used by workers for all repository operations
  gh     GitHub CLI — used by workers for PR / issue operations
  claude Claude Code CLI — the worker backend

Optional tools:

  bk     Buildkite CLI — needed for CI query features

Required credentials:

  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY  API key for Claude. The engine reads this from
                     the environment of the process that launches it
                     (i.e., the shell that double-clicks Boss.app, or
                     sets it in launchd / shell profile).

Uninstall:
  ~/Applications/Boss.app/Contents/Resources/bin/boss uninstall
  Add --purge-state to also remove ~/Library/Application Support/Boss/.

Manual uninstall (if the CLI is unavailable):
  rm -rf ~/Applications/Boss.app
  # Optional: rm -rf ~/Library/Application\ Support/Boss
EOF

exit 0
